rComments: Decent lecturer. Exams are not easy but not impossible.
Great professor for D21. Intelligent and takes the time to make sure you understand the course material. Midterms and Exams are lecture material and fair.
Very nice professor. Knows a lot about the course and about research in general. Very helpful and clear. Exams are extremely fair if you study.

She was so nice and helpful during office hours (and I went a lot)...but overall, this is just a hard course, the readings are tough, and hard to decipher if read just once or twice. I managed an average mark on the quiz and midterm only because I read the papers over a gazillion times. I wouldn't take this class over.

Horrible class, based solely on complicated research articles. The basics for this course were NOT covered in the B-level prerequisite, and she doesn't go over them in class. Though exam isn't cumulative, the material is very dense and hard to remember. Prof wouldn't post up lecture notes before class, but always about one hour after- senseless.
